      "comment_id" : 117362902,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "Obviously this is an old comment, but to anyone else reading this who has the same question; <code>Foo</code> is a pretty common term used in programming as a placeholder for a value that can change. It is useful when you&#39;re providing a generic example such as the one above, as <code>Foo</code> can be replaced by whichever object you&#39;re working with (in this case, a String). You may also see <code>Bar</code> used when there are multiple placeholders in an example."
    } ],
