    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>String ... and String[] are identical If you convert your list to array.</p>\n<p>using</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>Foo[] array = list.toArray(new Foo[list.size()]);\n</code></pre>\n<p>or</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>Foo[] array = new Foo[list.size()];\nlist.toArray(array);\n</code></pre>\n<p>then use that array as <code>String ...</code> argument to function.</p>\n<p>or as recommended since OpenJDK 6, use a zero-sized array:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>Foo[] array = list.toArray(new Foo[0]);\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
