    "question_id" : 16748470,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>For Java &gt; 8</p>\n<p>You can very well use the <code>toArray</code> method very simply, as in:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>String[] myParams = myList.toArray(String[]::new);\n</code></pre>\n<p>Streaming becomes really interesting when the elements of the List must be transformed, filtered or else before being converted to Array:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>String[] myMappedAndFilteredParams = myList.stream()\n                                 .map(param -&gt; param + &quot;some_added_stuff&quot;)\n                                 .filter(param -&gt; param.contains(&quot;some very important info&quot;))\n                                 .collect(toList())\n                                 .toArray(String[]::new);\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
